library(ggplot2)
data1 <- read.csv("insurance_cost.csv",
                           stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
hist(data1$age)

hist(data1$bmi)

hist(data1$charges)

charges

charges_mean <- round(mean(data1$charges))
charges_median <- round(median(data1$charges))

 ggplot(data1, 
       aes(charges)) +
  geom_density(fill="lightblue") +
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = charges_median)) +
  annotate("text", 
           x= charges_median, 
           y=0.00004,
           label=paste0("Median=", charges_median))+
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = charges_mean), 
             color="blue", linetype="dashed", size=1) +
  annotate("text", 
           x= charges_mean, 
           y=0.00001,
           label=paste0("Mean=", charges_mean), color="blue")+
  labs(title="    charges",x="charges", y = "Density")

box_plot charges sex

boxplot1 <- ggplot(data1, aes(x=sex, y=charges, fill=sex)) +
    geom_boxplot() +
    theme(
      legend.position="none",
      plot.title = element_text(size=11)
    ) +
    ggtitle("boxplot SEX") +
    xlab("sex") +
  ylab("charges")

print(boxplot1)

box_plot charges smoker

data1 %>% 
  filter(charges != 0) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=age, y= charges, color = region, fill = region, group = region)) + 
  geom_point() +
  facet_grid(. ~ region) +
  geom_smooth(method=lm, 
              fullrange = T, 
              alpha = 0.2,
              se=TRUE 
              )+
  theme_minimal() +
  ggtitle('        ') + 
  labs(y = '', x ='    ') +
  theme(
    title = element_text(size = 14), 
    axis.title.y = element_text(size=12) 
    )

data1 <- data1 %>% 
  mutate(
      age_group = case_when(
      age < 35 ~ "21-34",
      age >= 35 & age < 50 ~ "35-49",
      age >= 50 ~ "50+"
    ))
log_scale <- data1 %>% 
  filter(charges != 0) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=bmi, y= charges, color = age_group, fill = age_group, group = age_group)) + 
  geom_point() +
  facet_grid(. ~ age_group) +
  geom_smooth(method=lm, 
              fullrange = T, 
              alpha = 0.2,
              se=TRUE 
              )+
  theme_minimal() +
  ggtitle('      ') + 
  labs(y = '', x ='') +
  theme(
    title = element_text(size = 14), 
    axis.title.y = element_text(size=12) 
    )
print(log_scale)
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'
